title: For Sale/Trade:  Upgraded Bulgarian Arsenal milled SLR-95, 11 mags & 1860 rounds of ammo
postcontent:
Up for sale/trade I have a Bulgarian Arsenal Milled SLR-95 with 11 mags (10 steel & 1 polymer). and 1850 rounds of ammo.

Seems like every AK add I see claims to be "the best" AK ever made, but talk is cheap. The SLR-95 actually is the most rare, & highly sought after AK47 ever produced.  Here's the history;
The SLR-95 was made in the original ARSENAL factory in Bulgaria. This factory is world renouned for producing the highest quality AKs ever produced. The 95 has a milled reciever, milled fire control group and Steyr barrel. The 95 was originally milled to accept double stack magazines and was the only AK imported with zero US made parts. It was only imported from 1995-1998. All other Arsenal SLRs were produced in the U.S. from a satalite arsenal factory in Nevada. The Arsenal factory in nevada uses the same specs as the Bulgarian factory, and they produce some of the best AKs on the market, but they simply cannot compare to the AKs produced in the original Bulgarian factory. Simply do a little research on the web, and you'll understand why the SLR-95 is in a class of its own. You rarely see these things on armslist, and if you do, they're expensive & they go fast....why... because THEY ARE FREAKIN' BAD-ASS!!!

I've replaced the original front & rear sight with mepro-light tritium night sights, but I still have the original sights for all you pure-ist out there. I've also added a tapco T6 adjustable stock, hogue grip & aluminum front quad-rail, but again for you pure-ist I've still got the original thumbhole arsenal stock & foregrip. I'm also going to throw in 10 steel mags & 1860 rounds of 7.62x39 wolf & tulla hp & fmj, and for the right price/trade I'll even cerakote it the color or camo pattern of your choice. (to see cerakote gallery check out www.cerakotepros.com)

I'm not really sure I wanna let this thing go, but I am curious to see whats out there. Please text me any cash or trade offers to REDACTED. the worst I can say is no thanks. Please keep in mind I know what this package is worth, and I'll only trade for something of equal value. Also, I'm willing to throw in cash for the right trade. 
Thanks & good luck!

Please do a little research online, and know what you're looking at before making an offer.
